Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setFixedBudget(25.10)                                    setFixedBudget(25.10)

Name
       setFixedBudget  -  This  command fixes the budget for a particular path
       segment between partitions and start/end points and helps  in  reducing
       the distribution budget delay in the path segments

Syntax
       setFixedBudget

       [-help]

       {[{[{-from {list_of_pins} | -fromFlopsOf {hinst}} {-to {list_of_pins} |
       -toFlopsOf  {hinst}}]  | [-through {list_of_hinst}]} {-slack | -delay }
       [-add ] <value>] | [-reset ]}

       This command fixes the budget for a  particular  path  segment  between
       partitions  and start/end points and helps in reducing the distribution
       budget delay in the path segments.

       Note: Do not use this command with cycle-based timing budgeting.

       This command is valid only for the following segments:

              * Chip In -> Partition In

              * Start Point -> Partition In

              * Partition In -> Partition Out

              * Partition In -> End Point (FF D Pin) inside same partition

              * Start Point (FF Q Pin) inside same partition -> Partition Out

              * Partition Out -> Chip Out

              * Partition Out -> End Point

Parameters
       -add   Adds the slack/delay to previous value (Boolean, Optional)

       -help  Prints out the command usage

       <value>
              Presents delay or slack values (Float)

       -delay Specifies the delay value (Boolean, Optional)

       -from {list_of_pins}
              Presents the 'from pins' to be analyzed (String)

       -fromFlopsOf {hinst}
              Specifies the from hierarchical inst for which start pins to  be
              analyzed (String)

       -reset Resets all previously declared fixed budgets (Boolean, Optional)

       -slack Specifies the slack value (Boolean, Optional)

       -through {list_of_hinst}
              Specifies the hierarchical instances to be analyzed (String)

       -to {list_of_pins}
              Specifies the 'to pins' to be analyzed (String)

       -toFlopsOf {hinst}
              Specifies the to hierarchical inst for which end pins to be ana-
              lyzed (String)

Examples
       The  following  command  fixes  the budget of the hierarchical instance
       feed-through paths to the existing delay:

       setFixedBudget -through P5 -slack 0

       The following command gives a fixed clack of 1 to the paths  from  port
       'in'  to hierarchical instance input pin 'p4/in'; budgets will distrib-
       ute rest of the slack to other segments of the paths:

       setFixedBudget -from in -to P4/in -slack 1

       The following command fixes the delay of this segment to 0.5  from  the
       hierarchical  instance  input  pin  'p4/in' to the endpoint 'P4/FF1/D';
       budgets will be calculated for the whole path considering the path  de-
       lay of this segment as 0.5:

       setFixedBudget -from P4/in -to P4/FF1/D -delay 0.5

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the User Guide document.

